<br>
Raiding guilds do have enormous needs for cash. Those items that can be farmed are sold for plat to buy:<br>
<br>
1. Periodots<br>
2. Components for some of the turn-in quests<br>
3. Random resist gear<br>
4. Useful items the guild no longer farms (like res sticks)<br>
5. Equipping new members or server transfers more quickly as opposed to refarming old content.<br>
<br>
Amounts like 10 million are really not all that diffcult to gather. Each copy of a high end spell can generate 60-100k. The fact that officers can easily abuse the wealth a guild generates is a test of their character. Most are very honest. A few are not. Each member who belongs to a guild and discovers its leadership is siphoning off some items to effectively pay themselves a salary should either a) acecpt it or b) quit the guild.<br>
<br>
If enough members protested this type of behaviour, the guild could not exist. Kinda hard to farm the Elemetal planes with 3 people. . . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=galadonr>GaladonR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 582<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/12/03 6:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1935.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lol</span><hr size=1> OMG, the Mammoth Hide Cloak! I forgot all about that... those were the BEST days of EQ. I hope I see you likewise in SWG or EQ2... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morphstormhammer>MorphStormhammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/19/03 1:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1935.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Old Vazaelle person checking in</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the actions of certain former officers of TR are pretty repulsive.  I have been on Stormhammer since the day it opened.  I have been playing EQ since Beta II (just for background, including every PvP server for some period of time).  Stormhammer is definitely like swimming in a school of pirahnas.<br>
<br>
Facts (or opinions in some case) about Stormhammer<br>
<br>
The general age of the players (or should I say maturity) is generally pretty high.  There are very few cases of intentional training (with the notable exception of some very contested spawnsin Bastion of Thunder).<br>
<br>
There is alot more selling of the loot rights to high end no drop items then I have seen on other servers.  There are even a couple guilds that advertise their services to allow you to loot specific items for a price.  ST Keys (100k), Prismatic weapons (100k-150K), Willsapper, King Tormax Drops, Dain Drops, just about anything from this range of mob.<br>
<br>
There is a HUGE disparity between people that know their class and people that do not.  I have found that because of the Ebay effect described in posts about that people are more one dimensional.  They may have raid ability but cannot group with crud.  They may be able to group well, but have NEVER fought a Tier three mob.<br>
<br>
Population.  This is my favorite part, but may or may not be to most people's liking.  Every zone is empty.  You want the entrance to the Hole, its empty 85% of the time.  I would say that 95% of the prep PoP zones are ALWAYS empty.  Even the Tier 1 Planes in PoP are always empty.  PoI/PoD/PoN generally have from 4 to 10 people in them during prime time.  PoV is pretty much the only zone in the game where you will constantly find 20+ people at any given time.<br>
<br>
Its definitely different and has its plusses and minuses.<br>
<br>
Morph the Discerning<br>
Former Member of Agony 1.0 <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=1935.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1935.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1935.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1935.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1935.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1935.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1935.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><opti